-- Treasuries Rise as Bernanke Says Central Bank May Increase Debt Purchases
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   R e y n o l d s
-- 2010-12-06T00:07:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/treasuries-rise-as-bernanke-says-central-bank-may-increase-debt-purchases.html
Treasuries rose, snapping a three-day
drop, after Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke it was
possible the central bank will boost purchases of the
securities.  The benchmark 10-year yield dropped three basis points to
2.98 percent as of 9:05 a.m. in Tokyo, according to BGCantor
Market Data.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Reynolds at 
